  "text": "As a test of the derived expressions, we compare the mean intensity from Equation S35 [the discrete analog of (13)] to the average intensity computed from 1000 replications of the simulation. In each replication, an independent nonstationary scattering function is sampled from a multivariate Gaussian distribution consistent with the variance map in Fig. 2(A) , and an independent realization of acquisition noise is sampled from a Gaussian white noise process. The object variance map contains a clearly visible anechoic \"lesion\" in the center with a diameter of 1 cm, as seen in Fig. 2(B) . The comparison plot shown in Fig. 2(C) suggests very good agreement between the theoretical mean [CITATION_1] and the empirical average of the intensity signal. The average relative error across the plotted values is 3%.",
